1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the capacity of a communication system, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a communication system and its performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses a system consisting of multiple components and their interactions, which is relevant to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of information using radio frequency signals, which can be considered a form of multimedia communication. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - Although less likely, the paper may also fall under the category of computers and society as it discusses the impact of technology on communication and its potential applications.
